    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.12"/>
                
                <fw type="curatotiral">12</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">L. MATTHEWS WERNER • 1855 S. BAYSHORE DRIVE • MIAMI, FLORIDA</hi> 33133
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>The Big Dipper Constellation</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        June 13,1972.
                        Camp Ironwood
                        Harrison,Me.04040
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr.John Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln,Nebraska</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Margaret and I were so happy last night to welcome you into our home,in Maine,via The Dick Cavett Show. We enjoyed this much closeness to you last night far more than a year ago April. Last night we were prepared and waiting for you,a year ago we were in the Mountains of North Carolina and your <del><unclear>1</unclear></del><add>p</add>rogram was not listed. At the last moment I turned the <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> on and started twisting knobs and suddenly there you were!</p>
                
                <p>A delightful young couple with a fascinating,expressive beautiful four year old daughter have moved into a farm about a mile from us. He is a pr<del>eysx</del><add>off</add>es<add>s</add>ional Jewlery Maker and he and Margaret are having a great time sharing secrets of the trade and suggesting new ideas to each other. I had read some of your poetry to them and when they heard that your program was to be aired again they rushed down here to borrow your poetry books.</p> 
                
                <p>Next week Spike leaves for his third summer in India. He is becoming an expert on the life of The Indian Elephant, the backwoods Natives and I guess on the Geography<add>,</add> for he travels extensively. He has taken thousand of pictures and is writing a book. He teaches Speech and Hearing subjects at The Federal City College in Washington,<hi rend="caps">D.C.</hi></p>
                
                <p>Meade has married a widow with two sons 14 and 16 years old,so we have gotten two instant Grandchildren. We are delighted. Meade went to high school with the girl way back when! They will visit us here in July,and Spike the end of August.</p> 
                
                <p>We do wish that our trails would cross,but in the meanwhile we send our best wishes and</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Affectionate Greetings,</salute>
                    <salute><hi rend="caps">SELAH</hi>,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Matt</signed> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
